## SacredHealing — Cursor Rules (SQI 2050)
You are a coding agent working in this repository.
Primary mission: **remove hardcoded UI strings** and route all user-visible text through the existing i18n system.

### Non‑negotiable safety rules (DO NOT TOUCH)
- **Stripe**: Do not modify any code that calls Stripe checkout, creates checkout sessions, or references Stripe price IDs.
- **Affiliate tracking**: Do not modify affiliate IDs, referral params, tracking query params, or attribution logic.
- **Supabase auth**: Do not change `supabase.auth.*` flows unless explicitly asked for a specific bugfix.
- **Edge functions**: Do not change files under `supabase/functions/**` unless explicitly asked with an attached “FINAL” file.
- **RLS / DB policies**: Do not change policies/migrations unless explicitly asked.

### i18n system (use what this repo already uses)
- Locale files live in:
  - `src/i18n/locales/en.json`
  - `src/i18n/locales/sv.json`
  - (also `es.json`, `no.json`)
- Use the existing translation hook in the codebase (commonly `useTranslation()` from `react-i18next`):
  - `const { t } = useTranslation();`
- Replace all user-visible strings with `t('namespace.key')`.
- For dynamic strings, use interpolation:
  - Locale: `"greeting": "Namaste, {{name}}"`
  - Code: `t('dashboard.hero.greeting', { name })`
- Ensure **all new keys are added to both** `en.json` and `sv.json` at the same time (and any other supported locales if already present for that namespace).

### What counts as “user-visible strings”
Replace hardcoded strings in:
- JSX text nodes
- Button labels
- Placeholders (`placeholder=`)
- Titles (`title=`)
- Accessibility labels (`aria-label=`, `aria-describedby=` text)
- Toasts/alerts/modals/dialog content
- Empty states, loading text, error messages
- Menu items, tabs, headings, section labels

### Key naming convention (preferred)
Use a stable namespace pattern:
- `common.*` for shared buttons/errors/loading/empty states
- `auth.*`, `onboarding.*`, `dashboard.*`, `profile.*`, `healing.*`, `meditations.*`, `music.*`
- `community.*`, `journal.*`
- `quantumApothecary.*`, `soulscan.*`, `mantras.*`, `breathing.*`, `vedicAstrology.*`
- `tools.*` for tool/oracle pages
- `admin.*` for owner/admin pages

### SQI 2050 design tokens (when you touch UI)
Maintain/align to existing visual language:
- **Akasha Black**: `#050505`
- **Siddha Gold**: `#D4AF37`
- **Glass card**: `bg-white/[0.02] backdrop-blur-[40px] border border-white/[0.05] rounded-[40px]`
- **Gold title**: `text-[#D4AF37] font-black tracking-[-0.05em] [text-shadow:0_0_15px_rgba(212,175,55,0.3)]`
- **Body**: `text-white/60 leading-[1.6]`
- **Micro-label**: `uppercase text-[8px] tracking-[0.5em] text-white/60 font-extrabold`

### Search patterns to find hardcoded UI strings
Prefer ripgrep:
- `rg \"\\b[A-Z][a-z].*\" src/`
- `rg \">[^<{]*[A-Za-z][^<{]*<\" src/`
- `rg \"(placeholder|title|aria-label)=\\\"[^\\\"]+\\\"\" src/`
- `rg \"toast\\.(success|error|info|warning)\\(\\\"\" src/`
- `rg \"toast\\(\\{[^}]*title:\\s*\\\"\" src/`

### Workflow per file (strict)
1. Read the full file.
2. Identify all user-visible hardcoded strings.
3. Add i18n hook usage (`t`) if missing.
4. Replace strings with `t('...')`.
5. Add keys to `en.json` and `sv.json` (deep-merge; never delete existing keys).
6. Run typecheck/build or lints if available; fix introduced errors.

### Output expectations
- Keep changes minimal and mechanical.
- Never change runtime logic unless required to enable i18n.
- Do not “rewrite” large components unnecessarily.
